              <div class="main-content">
                <p><span data-contrast="none">Governor Gretchen Whitmer signed </span><a href="https://content.govdelivery.com/attachments/MIEOG/2020/04/02/file_attachments/1417518/EO%202020-35.pdf"><span data-contrast="none">Executive Order 2020-35</span></a><span data-contrast="none">,</span><span data-contrast="none"> which orders all K-12 school buildings to close for the remainder of the school year — unless restrictions are lifted — and ensures continuing of learning by setting guidelines for remote learning. District facilities may be used by public school employees and contractors for the purposes of facilitating learning at a distance while also practicing social distancing.</span><span data-ccp-props='{"134233279":true,"201341983":0,"335559740":276}'> </span></p>
<p>We will communicate to our community using School Messenger emails and Unified Classroom.</p>
<p>Again, be sure that our emails are not going to junk or spam folders and that your family has your log in information for Unified Classroom.</p>
